Interior Secretary Dirk Kempthorne announced a proposal to list the polar bear as a threatened species under the Endangered Species Act because of the loss of its sea ice habitat from global warming.
The Bush administration will examine whether a growing number of species, including polar bears affected by thinning sea ice, are at risk from global warming and need federal protection ,.
The federal agency responsible for protecting Arctic polar bears has barred two Alaska scientists, a move that environmentalists say is censorship.
